# Original AI-Generated Project Summary (Unvalidated Draft)

**What it is:** A financial monitoring dashboard that shows income/outcome KPIs,
a monthly income-vs-outcome chart, and a profit-percentage trend chart for a
business, with filtering by B2B/B2C segment.

## Architecture
- **Frontend** (`frontend/`): React 19 + TypeScript, built with Vite, styled
  with Tailwind v4 + a shadcn-style component system, charts via `recharts`.
- **Backend** (`backend/`): FastAPI, single router file, no database — all
  data is procedurally generated mock data.
- Frontend and backend run as separate Docker services (`docker-compose.yml`),
  frontend on 5173, backend on 8000, talking over `/api` via Vite's dev proxy.

## Data flow (as initially understood)
`App.tsx` fetches `GET /api/metrics` on mount, then runs the response through
`computeKPIs()` and `computeMonthlyData()` to derive the KPI row and chart
data client-side. Every endpoint in `routes.py` independently calls
`generate_mock_movements(seed=42)` — there's no real persistence layer.

## Backend API surface
`/health`, `/api/metrics`, `/api/metrics/facets`, `/api/metrics/summary`,
`/api/metrics/categories/top`, `/api/metrics/comparison`, `/api/metrics/alerts`,
`/api/metrics/b2b`, `/api/metrics/b2c`.

## Testing
Both sides have test coverage — `backend/tests/test_routes.py` and
`frontend/src/lib/financial-utils.test.ts` — but only `financial-utils.ts`
is tested on the frontend.

## Flagged for verification (unconfirmed at draft time)
- `frontend/src/lib/mock-data.ts` appears unused — needs confirming.
- `backend/requirements.txt` has no version pins.
- `debugpy` sits alongside production dependencies with no dev/prod split.




# Validation Steps

- Ran the app locally (`docker compose up --build`) and inspected the
  Network tab to confirm the dashboard is driven by a live call to
  `GET /api/metrics`, not static data.
- Ran `grep -rn "mockMovements" .` in `frontend/src` — confirmed
  `mock-data.ts` is unused (only match is its own declaration).
- Read `backend/app/routes.py` in full — confirmed 9 endpoints and
  filtering logic exist but assessed real usage separately (below).
- Read `backend/requirements.txt` — confirmed no version pins and no
  dev/runtime dependency separation (`debugpy` alongside `fastapi`).
- Ran `find components -name "*.test.*"` in `frontend/src` — confirmed
  zero test files for the five dashboard components.
- Ran `grep -rn "fetch(" .` in `frontend/src` — confirmed only one
  network call exists (`/api/metrics`, no query params), meaning 8 of
  9 backend endpoints and all filter/sort params are unused.
- Manually tested the dashboard UI — confirmed no filtering, sorting,
  or clickable elements exist; only chart tooltips on hover.
- Compared the rendered header ("2024 - Full Year") against the chart
  x-axis range (Aug 2025 – Jun 2026) — confirmed a mismatch.